Sasini of Kenya Reverses Gain, Falls for First Day in Three

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-06-09T13:20:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/sasini-of-kenya-heads-for-highest-in-week-as-tea-prices-rise.html
Sasini Ltd. (STCL) , a Kenyan tea and coffee
producer fell for the first time in three days, reversing
earlier gains.  The stock dropped 0.4 percent to 12.25 shillings by the 3
p.m. close in the capital, Nairobi.  Earlier, Sasini shares rose after tea prices at yesterday’s
auction in the Kenyan port city of Mombasa climbed to an average
of $2.65 per kilogram (2.2 pounds) from $2.63 a week earlier,
Tea Brokers East Africa Ltd. said in an e-mailed report. Kenya
is the world’s biggest producer of black tea.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  